L: k^2 \to k^2
a,b,c,d \in k
L(u,v) = (au+bv, cu+dv),
L
L(1,0)
L(0,1)
k^2
a,b,c,d\in k
L
(u,v)\in k^2
L(1,0)=(a,c),\qquad L(0,1)=(b,d)
\begin{align*} L(u,v)&=L(u\cdot(1,0)+v\cdot (0,1))\\\\ &=u\cdot L(1,0)+v\cdot L(0,1)\\\\ &=u\cdot(a,c)+v\cdot(b,d)\\\\ &=(au,cu)+(bv,dv)\\\\ &=(au+bv,cu+dv) \end{align*}
